44CachedSVGFont::CachedSVGFont(CachedResourceRequest&& request, PAL::SessionID sessionID, const CookieJar* cookieJar, const Settings& settings)
45 : CachedFont(WTFMove(request), sessionID, cookieJar, Type::SVGFontResource)
46 , m_externalSVGFontElement(nullptr)
47 , m_settings(settings)
48{
49}
50
51CachedSVGFont::CachedSVGFont(CachedResourceRequest&& request, CachedSVGFont& resource)
52 : CachedSVGFont(WTFMove(request), resource.sessionID(), resource.cookieJar(), resource.m_settings)
53{
54}
55
56RefPtr<Font> CachedSVGFont::createFont(const FontDescription& fontDescription, const AtomString& remoteURI, bool syntheticBold, bool syntheticItalic, const FontFeatureSettings& fontFaceFeatures, FontSelectionSpecifiedCapabilities fontFaceCapabilities)
57{
58 ASSERT(firstFontFace(remoteURI));
59 return CachedFont::createFont(fontDescription, remoteURI, syntheticBold, syntheticItalic, fontFaceFeatures, fontFaceCapabilities);
60}
61
62FontPlatformData CachedSVGFont::platformDataFromCustomData(const FontDescription& fontDescription, bool bold, bool italic, const FontFeatureSettings& fontFaceFeatures, FontSelectionSpecifiedCapabilities fontFaceCapabilities)
63{
64 if (m_externalSVGDocument)
65 return FontPlatformData(fontDescription.computedPixelSize(), bold, italic);
66 return CachedFont::platformDataFromCustomData(fontDescription, bold, italic, fontFaceFeatures, fontFaceCapabilities);
67}
68
69bool CachedSVGFont::ensureCustomFontData(const AtomString& remoteURI)
70{
71 if (!m_externalSVGDocument && !errorOccurred() && !isLoading() && m_data) {
72 bool sawError = false;
73 {
74 // We may get here during render tree updates when events are forbidden.
75 // Frameless document can't run scripts or call back to the client so this is safe.
76 m_externalSVGDocument = SVGDocument::create(nullptr, m_settings, URL());
77 auto decoder = TextResourceDecoder::create("application/xml");
78
79 ScriptDisallowedScope::DisableAssertionsInScope disabledScope;
80
81 m_externalSVGDocument->setContent(decoder->decodeAndFlush(m_data->data(), m_data->size()));
82 sawError = decoder->sawError();
83 }
84
85 if (sawError)
86 m_externalSVGDocument = nullptr;
87 if (m_externalSVGDocument)
88 maybeInitializeExternalSVGFontElement(remoteURI);
89 if (!m_externalSVGFontElement || !firstFontFace(remoteURI))
90 return false;
91 if (auto convertedFont = convertSVGToOTFFont(*m_externalSVGFontElement))
92 m_convertedFont = SharedBuffer::create(WTFMove(convertedFont.value()));
93 else {
94 m_externalSVGDocument = nullptr;
95 m_externalSVGFontElement = nullptr;
96 return false;
97 }
98 }
99
100 return m_externalSVGDocument && CachedFont::ensureCustomFontData(m_convertedFont.get());
101}
102
103SVGFontElement* CachedSVGFont::getSVGFontById(const String& fontName) const
104{
105 ASSERT(m_externalSVGDocument);
106 auto elements = descendantsOfType<SVGFontElement>(*m_externalSVGDocument);
107
108 if (fontName.isEmpty())
109 return elements.first();
110
111 for (auto& element : elements) {
112 if (element.getIdAttribute() == fontName)
113 return &element;
114 }
115 return nullptr;
116}
117
118SVGFontElement* CachedSVGFont::maybeInitializeExternalSVGFontElement(const AtomString& remoteURI)
119{
120 if (m_externalSVGFontElement)
121 return m_externalSVGFontElement;
122 String fragmentIdentifier;
123 size_t start = remoteURI.find('#');
124 if (start != notFound)
125 fragmentIdentifier = remoteURI.string().substring(start + 1);
126 m_externalSVGFontElement = getSVGFontById(fragmentIdentifier);
127 return m_externalSVGFontElement;
128}
129
130SVGFontFaceElement* CachedSVGFont::firstFontFace(const AtomString& remoteURI)
131{
132 if (!maybeInitializeExternalSVGFontElement(remoteURI))
133 return nullptr;
134
135 if (auto* firstFontFace = childrenOfType<SVGFontFaceElement>(*m_externalSVGFontElement).first())
136 return firstFontFace;
137 return nullptr;
138}
